    "Body": " Aegis Weapon System Engineer A-P-T Research - Dahlgren, VA Apply Now Job Details Full-timeEstimated: $84,000 - $110,000 a year Benefits Health Insurance Qualifications CISSP-ISSMP Bachelor's Degree Full Job Description MDA Position for an intermediate engineer at Dahlgren Experience Requirements: The applicant must have 5+ years of relevant experience along with a bachelor\u2019s degree. Job Responsibilities: Support the ABQ government safety lead with the management of the MDA system safety programs for MDA/ABS. Support government Quality, Safety and Mission Assurance Lead. Participate in the drafting of Requirements Applicability Matrix (RAM) and MDA Mission Assurance Provisions (MAP). Reviews and update requirement as programs mature. Ensures safety programs are in compliance with MDA MAP, System Safety Program Plans, MDA Integrated System Safety Management Plans (ISSMP) and MIL-STD-882E. Review and/or write Safety MIL-STD-882E assessments. Brief ABS program office leadership on status of safety programs and Works with the program office, government Principle For Safety (PFS) and contractors to resolve safety issues. Tracks system safety program schedules to ensure deadlines are being met. Host quarterly system safety working groups to obtain status updates and address concerns with government safety counterparts. Perform System Safety Risk Assessments (SSRA) and attend meetings to Support MDA flight tests. Support System Safety Working Groups (SSWG), System Engineering Working Groups (SEWG) and other required meetings for ABS programs. Support Weapon System Explosive Safety Review Boards (WSESRB) and Software System Safety Review Panels (SSSTRP) by reviewing Technical Data Packages (TDPs) and slides. Provided inputs as necessary. Briefs program office directors to obtain risk acceptance prior baseline deployment. Works with program offices and government safety personnel to address and close out WSESRB findings and obtain WSESRB concurrence to deploy AEGIS baselines. Ensures safety programs are in line with Master Program Plans and that programs meet all requirements for their Operational Capability Baseline (OCB) deployment dates. Ensure existing programs are maintained and updated in accordance with MDA standards throughout their life cycle. Support APT counterparts in ABG (SM-3 missile) and ABZ (Aegis Ashore Facility) safety programs as needed. APT is an employee-owned company specializing in conducting safety analyses for the U.S. Government. APT offers competitive salaries, advancement opportunities, and excellent benefits. APT is proud to be an Affirmative Action/Equal Opportunity Employer. APT provides equal employment opportunity for all persons, in all facets of employment. APT maintains a drug-free workplace and performs background checks. We encourage veterans, disabled veterans, and disabled individuals to apply for any open position for which they feel they are qualified. Accessibility APT is committed to expanding access to employment for people with disabilities and disabled veterans. If you are a qualified individual with a disability or a disabled veteran, and your disability prevents you from applying, please advise what reasonable accommodation APT can provide to assist you in applying for one of our open positions. Please visit our company website at www.apt-research.com for contact information. Reasonable accommodations are considered on a case-by-case basis. Please note that only those inquiries concerning a request for reasonable accommodation for applying for a specific posted position will be responded to. Requests will be kept confidential and shared strictly on a need-to-know basis. Applicants selected will be subject to a security investigation and must meet eligibility requirements for access to classified information. All resumes will be treated in strictest confidence. Please contact recruit@apt-research.com for any questions or concerns. Requisition Number: 2020-07 "
